text:
Hi, the next date for our next FoC meetup will be 25 September 16:00 UTC and this time we will do a FoC wikijam!
Our FoC meetups so far have been an hour, but I do wonder if that's enough, so I appreciate some feedback on how we will setup our wikijam since I don't have experience with it. 
Perhaps the time can also be used to just setup rough drafts for articles which will be worked on further after the meetup.

text: Perhaps it's wise to already make a list of wiki-articles that we want to have written in that wiki-jam session? Anyone else got ideas on how to get the most out of that meetup?
